SIMPLE: hussy
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hussy
<hw>Hus"sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Contr. fr.
<ets>huswife</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A housewife or
housekeeper.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A worthless woman or girl; a forward wench; a jade;
-- used as a term of contempt or reproach.</def>
<rj><au>Grew.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A pert girl; a frolicsome or sportive young woman;
-- used jocosely.</def> <rj><au>Goldsmith.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hussy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hussy
